# Known-good SHA-256 hashes for romance scam statistics source documents
#
# Format: <hash>  <file-id>  # <description or source label>
#
# Notes:
# - PDFs (IC3, FTC CSN) produce stable hashes — a mismatch indicates the
#   document was replaced or tampered with.
# - HTML pages produce volatile hashes — content changes on every crawl due
#   to ads, analytics, timestamps. A mismatch is expected; manual review
#   confirms whether the actual article content changed.
# - GONE (HTTP 403/404) sources need manual investigation — the URL may
#   have moved, or the site may block automated requests.
#
# To add a new hash, run verify-sources.sh and follow its instructions.
# To update a hash after a source has been verified as legitimately updated,
# replace the hash value (do not delete the line — the file-id is the unique key).

